 and survived the First World War.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSoldierszCanadavCorrespondence. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918vPersonal narratives, Canadian. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xCampaignszBelgium. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xCampaignszFrance. 7aHISTORY / Military / World War I.2bisacsh1 aBennett, Y.A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077481610640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774816106423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774816106/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  a978-3-11-141860-5  University of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000c2013d2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles